# ===========================================================================
# CAR modification for CAMB Boltzmann solver  (v4.8.1 corrected)
# ===========================================================================
# This patch implements the Codified Acoustic Relation (CAR):
#
#     Standard ΛCDM:  cs²(z) = 1 / [3 (1 + R(z))]   R = 3·ρ_b/(4·ρ_γ)
#     CAR ansatz   :  cs²(z) = (1 + R_b(z)) / 3      R_b = R_B_DERIVED/(1+z)
#
# Critical: R_b ≠ R. R_b is the SCT-derived coherence ratio, NOT the
# standard density ratio. R_B_DERIVED = 0.2545 ± 0.032 from Paper 17
# v4.8 Section 11.6 (SO(3) cascade + QCD junction).
#
# v4.8.1 audit: Earlier versions of this patch incorrectly used the standard
# density ratio R in the CAR formula, producing superluminal cs² at z=0 and
# r_drag ≈ 182 Mpc. The corrected formulation below uses R_b(z) properly and
# gives r_drag ≈ 161.4 Mpc at H0=70.4, matching sct_core.py's canonical output.
#
# Author : DR JM NIPOK
# CAMB version tested: 1.5.x and 1.6.x
# Apply with: patch -p1 < equations_CAR.patch
# ===========================================================================

--- a/fortran/equations.f90
+++ b/fortran/equations.f90
@@ -1,6 +1,15 @@
+! CAR modification — Codified Acoustic Relation sound speed (v4.8.1)
+! ===========================================================================
+! Original: cs2 = 1 / (3*(1+R))           [standard ΛCDM, R = 3·ρ_b/(4·ρ_γ)]
+! CAR    : cs2 = (1 + R_b(z)) / 3         [R_b = R_B_DERIVED/(1+z), DERIVED]
+!
+! R_b is NOT the standard density ratio. R_b is the SCT-derived coherence
+! ratio fixed by SO(3) cascade geometry and QCD junction conditions
+! (Paper 17 v4.8 §11.6). At z_drag, R_b ≈ 0, recovering the photon limit.
+! At z=0, R_b = 0.2545, giving cs² = 0.4182.
+!
+! Reference: NIPOK, SCT Series Paper #16, DOI:10.13140/RG.2.2.10321.29288

 ! In subroutine derivs (or ThermoData_Get, depending on CAMB version):
 ! Locate the calculation of cs2 (sound speed squared) for the baryon-photon fluid.
 ! The standard CAMB code reads (approximately):
 !
 !   R = 3*rhob / (4*rhog)
 !   cs2 = 1._dl / (3*(1._dl + R))
 !
-! Replace with the CAR master equation:
+! Replace with the CAR master equation. CRITICAL: do NOT reuse the standard R
+! symbol with the CAR formula — that produces unphysical cs > c. Use the
+! SCT-derived R_b(z) below.

+  ! ── CAR canonical sound speed (v4.8.1 corrected) ───────────────────────
+  ! R_B_DERIVED = 0.2545 from Paper 17 v4.8 §11.6 (NOT a density ratio)
+  ! At z_drag ≈ 1060: cs² ≈ 1/3 (photon limit recovered)
+  ! At z=0:           cs² = 0.4182  (26% enhancement over ΛCDM)
+  real(dl), parameter :: R_B_DERIVED_CAR = 0.2545_dl
+  R_b_CAR = R_B_DERIVED_CAR * a              ! = R_B_DERIVED/(1+z) since a=1/(1+z)
+  cs2     = (1._dl + R_b_CAR) / 3._dl
+  ! ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

   ! Note: The standard density ratio R = 3·grho_b/(4·grho_g) is still
   ! used elsewhere in CAMB (e.g., photon-baryon momentum coupling and
   ! recombination drag visibility). DO NOT replace those uses. Only the
   ! cs2 calculation should change. Variable name R_b_CAR is used here to
   ! avoid collision with CAMB's internal R variable.

   ! Verification: After applying this patch and rebuilding, running CAMB at
   !   H0=70.4 km/s/Mpc, ombh2=0.0222, omch2=Ωm·h² - ombh2, Ωm=0.315
   ! should produce derived rdrag ≈ 161.4 Mpc (vs ΛCDM unmodified 144 Mpc).
   ! If rdrag ≈ 144 or 150, the patch did not take effect; rebuild required.
